      "narrative": {
        "News": "France - INEOS - Lavera: the 36,500 bpd FCC was restarted dur- ing the morning of July 12 (GMT). Increased activity began at the unit on July 9 and the unit was shut on June 15.",
        "Ongoing Events": "Italy - ENI - Milazzo: the 111,000 bpd CDU was restarted during the morning of July 9 (GMT). Increased activity began at the unit on July 7 and the unit was shut on June 26. Also, increased activ- ity began at the 12,000 bpd catalytic reformer during the morning of July 9 (GMT), but remained below normal operational levels thus far. The unit was shut on June 21. Planned work was repor- ted, according to sources. France - Rhone Energies - Fos-sur-Mer: the 32,630 bpd FCC was shut during the evening of July 5 (GMT). Decreased scrubber activity began at that time. Also, elevated flaring began at the re- finery during the morning of July 5 (GMT). The company warned of flaring as a result of an unspecified unit shutdown via a local com- munity notice. Spain - Repsol - Cartagena: a hydrogen plant was restarted dur- ing the morning of February 13 following a brief outage. The unit was shut on February 11. Also at the refinery, the 100,000 bpd CDU was shut during the evening of January 26 and remained off- line.",
        "Planned Maintenance": "Greece - Helleniq Petroleum*: work at the Aspropyrgos refinery is postponed to the first half of 2026, according to Bloomberg. The work is expected to start in February. France - TotalEnergies – Feyzin: a turnaround is expected in 2027, according to Bloomberg. Spain - Repsol - Bilbao: planned work on the coker is expected in 2026. Exact dates are unknown but are expected to take at least 40 days. Spain - Moeve - San Roque: unspecified partial work is expected in Q4, according to sources."
      }
