      "narrative": {
        "News": "Hungary - MOL - Duna: the 21,100 bpd coker was shut during the evening of July 11 (GMT). The unit was recently restarted on July 10 after being shut on June 6. The 72,300 bpd CDU and the 74,000 bpd VDU were shut following a fire on October 20 and re- mained offline. Slovakia - Slovnaft - Bratislava: the 16,000 bpd catalytic re- former was restarted during the evening of July 12 (GMT). Also, in- creased activity continued at the 55,000 bpd CDU since the after- noon of July 11 (GMT), but remained below normal operational levels thus far. Both units were shut on June 25. Moreover, the 16,000 bpd naphtha hydrotreater was shut on July 3 and remained offline.",
        "Ongoing Events": "Poland - Orlen - Plock: the 70,000 bpd hydrocracker and a hy- drogen plant were restarted during the morning of July 1. In- creased activity began at the units on June 25. The hydrocracker was shut on May 13 and the hydrogen plant was shut on May 15. Also, a 69,500 bpd CDU and a 51,000 bpd VDU were shut on June 27 and the 22,000 bpd visbreaker was shut on May 14. The units remained offline. Planned work was expected to begin mid-May, according to sources.",
        "Planned Maintenance": "Poland - Orlen - Plock: planned work on a hydrocracker was ex- pected to begin mid-May, according to sources. Lithuania - Orlen Lietuva- Mazekai: unspecified planned work on a number of units is expected to start in Q1 and Q2. More main- tenance is expected in 2027, according to sources."
